Philippine Stocks: MRC Allied, Philippine Bank of Communications

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-06-07T04:24:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-07/philippine-stocks-mrc-allied-philippine-bank-of-communications.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of as the noon close in  Manila .  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index fell 0.5 percent to
4,236.45, the lowest level since May 26.  MRC Allied Inc. (MRC)  , a developer, increased 7.6
percent to 71 centavos, the sharpest gain since Jan. 10. MRC
Allied said it received a proposal from an Australian company to
develop its mining property in the southern Philippine province
of Surigao del Sur.  Under the proposal, the Sydney-based company and a unit of
MRC Allied will form a venture listed on the Australian Stock
Exchange, with the Surigao property as its primary asset,
according to a stock-exchange filing.  Philippine Bank of Communications (PBC PM) surged 48
percent to 74.05 pesos, the highest close since Sept. 2, 2005.
 ISM Communications Corp. (ISM)   is in “preliminary” talks to
acquire a controlling stake in  Philippine Bank of
Communications (PBC) , a stock-exchange filing showed. ISM gained 2
percent to 4.08 pesos, the highest level since Jan. 17.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
